How much is it to take a kitten home everything included?

@team10iscoolman Hi! Our kitten adoption fee is $100. If you don't have a carrier, we sell cardboard ones for $5. You find out more about what's included in our adoptions on our website: friendsofstrays.org

There's only a short amount of time until Valentine's day, and Gabrielle is hoping you'll take her home to celebrate! This independent, relaxed, sweet kitty is the ultimate lover girl once she feels comfortable in her space. She's fine with chillin' on her own but loves when company comes around for a visit! She currently resides in our lobby at our Sherwood location, along with the beautiful pink corsage decorating her face. Designed by Sweet Pickles Designs, these corsages come in lots of different colors as well as a handful of bowtie options as well! These cute and fabulous accessories are sold right in our Shelter! Pick one up for each of your cats or come say "Hi" to Gabrielle. We look forward to seeing you this weekend.

A question, is there a trick to get cat in a cage to take her to the vet?

@nankoehrsen One of the things that we do with our more carrier-fearing cats is to slowly build up their confidence in their carriers. We try to leave the carrier out and open all the time, so the kitty has access. Then we place treats inside the carrier, so the cat associates it with something good. Don't close the door immediately - give your cat some time before you actually have to transport them anywhere. Hopefully then they'll associate the carrier with good things instead of bad!
@catadoptpdx thank you.

This sugar-dipped elderbull is Vera (#A905655) and, boy, is she yummy! Vera has an easy mellow energy, and if you're looking for a couch companion to cuddle up with, Vera's the ideal candidate! She's eager to please and she was very attentive to her handler and followed her around the yard, right by her side. It's no mystery why she's a volunteer favorite at the shelter right now. She has quite a fan club, and any volunteers reading this, please check in with your comments below! Fall in love with Vera at 4800 Imhoff Place, Martinez, CA.
